<DOC><DOCNO> AP880702-0122 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-02-88 1519EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Gradl     07-02 0133</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Obit-Gradl,0138</SECOND><HEAD>Berlin CDU Co-Founder Dies at Age 84</HEAD><DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Johann Baptist Gradl, a former federal governmentminister and respected West Berlin politician, died following along illness, city officials said Saturday. Gradl was 84.   Gradl, who died late Friday night, helped found Berlin'sChristian Democratic Union party in 1945.   He fled the Soviet-controlled sector of the divided city intoWest Berlin two years later, after disagreements with communistauthorities.   Gradl was a member of the West German parliament, the Bundestag,from 1957 to 1980, representing West Berlin.   He also served as the federal minister for German exiles in1965-66.   From 1969 to 1972, he was chairman of the Bundestag Committeefor German-German Relations.   West German Chancellor Helmut Kohl on Saturday said Gradl had``devoted his life to German reunification.''</TEXT></DOC>